4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, the proceeds from the
6 simplified sellers use tax (SSUT) are distributed to
7 the State General Fund, Education Trust Fund, and the
8 counties and municipalities in this state.
9 This bill would require each county and
10 municipality to distribute a portion of SSUT proceeds
11 to the local boards of education serving students in
12 the respective jurisdictions.
13
14
15 A BILL
16 TO BE ENTITLED
17 AN ACT
18
19 Relating to the simplified sellers use tax; to amend
20 Section 40-23-197, Code of Alabama 1975, to require each
21 county and municipality to allocate a portion of its
22 simplified sellers use tax proceeds to the local boards of
23 education; and to repeal Section 40-23-197.1, Code of Alabama
24 1975, regarding monthly distributions of simplified sellers
25 use tax proceeds.
26 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
27 Section 1. Section 40-23-197, Code of Alabama 1975, is
28 amended to read as follows:
